data.text:
Choose a Staff Member:

Hanna Kiefer

Title

Student Assistant Coach

Alma Mater, Year

Stetson University, 2022

Year at Stetson

First Year

Playing Career

Played 95 rounds of competitive golf over five seasons at Stetson, finishing her career with a 75.57 scoring average

Spring 2022

Opened her final season with a tie for 13th at the First Coast Classic, posting three consecutive rounds of 77

Followed up with a final round 74 at the UNF Collegiate

Finished tied for 29th at the Spring Break Shootout after posting rounds of 74-75-75

Got off to a slow start at the Babs Steffens Invitational, but finished with an even par 72 in the final round to tie for 22nd in her last home event

Earned her best finish, a tie for third, in cold and blustery conditions at the Hoya Invitational, posting rounds of 73-74-78

Finished tied for 23rd at the ASUN Championship after carding rounds of 74-76-79 at Kinderlou Forest Country Club

Finished her final season with a 74.97 scoring average over 30 rounds of competition.

Fall 2021

Led the Hatters with a 73.25 scoring average in 12 rounds of competition

Opened the season with a two-under par round of 69 at the Golfweek Fall Challenge before posting consecutive rounds of 74 to finish tied for 12th with a four-over par total of 217

Earned her second top 20 finish with a three-over par total of 219 at the Lady Paladin Invitational to tie for 17th

Had her best round of the fall, a four-under par 68, in the opening round of the FIU Pat Bradley Invitational

Followed with rounds of 77 and 75 to finish tied for 16th with a four-over par total of 220

Closed the fall with a seven-over par performance at the Palmetto Intercollegiate that included rounds of 73-76-74 to tie for 32nd

Spring 2021

Played in three events, posting a 77.22 scoring average over nine rounds of competition

Made her season debut at the Kiawah Island Classic where she posted round of 71-73-79 to finish with a seven-over par score of 223

Finished tied for 17th out of 210 players

Struggled in the UNF Collegiate, posting rounds of 82-83-79 for a 28-over par 244 to finish tied for 79th of 92 players

Opened the ASUN Championship with a 71 before posting rounds of 77 and 80 to finish tied for 13th of 39 players with a 12-over par total of 228

Spring 2020

Opened the spring season with a career-best round of 68 in the JU Amelia Island Collegiate

Followed up with rounds of 70 and 73 to force a playoff, capturing medalist honors on the second playoff hole

Finished with a five-under par score of 211 to top a field of 80 players

Earned her second career ASUN Player of the Week award for her performance at the Amelia Island Collegiate

Continued her strong play at the Kiawah Island Classic with rounds of 74-70-75 to finish tied for 19th of 264 players with a three-over par score of 219

Opened play at the Dr. Dennis Thompson Invitational in Hawai'i with a round of 71

Posted rounds of 77 and 70 to finish tied for 11th among 92 players with a two-over par score of 218

Finished her junior season with a 73.64 scoring average over 22 rounds of competition

Posted an overall record of 590-112-14 according to Golfweek with an overall rating of 74.9

Was named to the ASUN Academic Honor Roll

Fall 2019

Opened the season with a 71 at the Golfweek Program Challenge

Followed up with rounds of 75 and 77 to finish with a seven-over par score of 223, tied for 24th of 78 players

After opening the Dartmouth Invitational with a 77, posted a 71 in the second and final round to finish with a four-over par score of 148, good for 13th in a 79 player field

Posted rounds of 79-79-78 in the Jacksonville Classic for a 20-over par 236 to finish 50th of 74 players

Posted rounds of 76 and 74 in the rain-shortened Hatter Classic to finish tied for 16th of 47 players with a six-over par 150

Closed out the fall season with a strong performance at the FIU Pat Bradley Invitational, finishing tied for 10th out of 90 players to help the Hatters to a tournament title

Posted rounds of 74-71-70 for a one-under par score of 211

Summer 2019

Played in the 90th Womenâ€™s State Amateur at the Ritz-Carlton Member Club in Bradenton, advancing to match play with scores of 83 and 74

Finished tied for ninth.

Spring 2019

Posted a 76.5 scoring average over 26 rounds of competition for the full season

Opened the spring schedule with a nine-over par score of 225 at the Kiawah Island Classic to finish tied for 65th out of 254 players

Posted rounds of 77-76-74 at the UNF Collegiate to finish tied for 37th out of 90 players with an 11-over par 227

Earned a top 20 finish in the LadyCat Invitational with rounds of 75-76-75, tying for 19th out of 86 players with a 10-over par 226

Opened the Babs Steffens Hatter Classic with a round of 72 before posting scores of 76 and 80 to finish tied for 12th of 71 players with a 12-over par 228

Earned a third consecutive top 20 finish with a 20-over par 236 at the Georgia Southern Strutter Gus Invitational, finishing 12th of 41 players

Struggled at the ASUN Championship with rounds of 84-83-80 to finish 22nd of 35 players with a 28-over par 247

Was named to the ASUN Academic Honor Roll

Fall 2018

Made her season debut at the USA Intercollegiate, posting consecutive rounds of 68 before a final round 78 left her tied for sixth of 93 players with a two-under par 214

Was named ASUN Player of the Week for that performance

Got off to a slow start at the Pinehurst Challenge with an opening 81, but followed up with rounds of 78 and 72 to finish with a 15-over par 231 to tie for 50th out of 92 players

Posted rounds of 78 and 77 in the Saint Leo Invitational to tie for 26th with an 11-over par score of 155

Spring 2018

Made her collegiate debut at the UNF Collegiate with rounds of 82-81-73

Finished tied for 64th of 93 players with a 20-over par 236

Posted scores of 78-78-76 in the Babs Steffens Hatter Invitational to finish tied for 10th of 70 players with a 16-over par score of 232

Tied for 16th in her first ASUN Championship, which was shortened by weather, posting scores of 78 and 80 for a 14-over par 158

Posted a 78.25 scoring average over eight rounds of competition

Junior Career

Came to the United States after her sophomore year at Sportgymnasium Erfurt to attend Hilton Head Prep in South Carolina

Did not play prep golf, but was highly successful on the amateur circuits

Was named the Hurricane Junior Golf Tour (HJGT) Girls 14-18 Player of the Year in 2016 after winning six of the 11 events she competed in

Posted a career-best round of 67 in 2017 and had a round of 69 in 2016

Graduated with a 3.8 overall GPA

Chose Stetson over Coastal Carolina

Personal Information

Hanna is the daughter of Stephanie Kiefer

Was born on June 11, 1999, in Karlsruhe, Germany

Has two brothers - Niklas (27) and Frederik (25) - and one sister, Valerie (29)

Her mother was a member of the German national golf team and currently competes on the senior national team in Germany

Enjoys skiing, wake boarding and weight lifting

Received her undergraduate degree in Secondary Education

Is currently working toward a Master's degree in Marriage, Couple and Family Counseling
